.TH SHELL " 16 August 2024" "Simple Shell" "man page"

.SH NAME
.B simple shell
\- Minimalistic Unix command line interpreter


.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.RI [command] " " [argument]

.SH DESCRIPTION

Minimalistic Unix command line interpreter that executes commands from a user terminal. The
shell reads commands from standard intput and executes them.

.SH INSTALLATION

Compile the files using the following command:

.nf
.B gcc -Wall -Werror -pedantic super_simple_shell.c execute.c -o super_simple_shell
.fi

Then, run the following command to open the simple shell:

.nf
.B ./hsh
.fi

.SH LIBRARIES USED
The following libraries and definitions are used in this project:

.nf
#define BUFFER_SIZE 1024
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <unistd.h>
#include <sys/types.h>
#include <sys/wait.h>
.fi

.SH USE
The simple shell is a Unix command line interpreter.
It will interpreters the first word as a command, and the following as the series of arguments.

Examples:
.nf
.B ./hsh
$ ls -l
$ pwd
$ exit
.fi

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shell
.BR bash

